AGI - Fifteen years after the tragedy of the earthquake that hit L'Aquila and 56 other municipalities of the seismic crater last night, shortly after 21:30, it started from Via XX September the commemorative torch of the 309 victims who, after a stop in front of the student's house, ended in Piazzale Paoli where the Memory Park is located with a participation of about 1400 people. The City of L'Aquila, with the participation of the Family Association victims of the earthquake, organized the initiative to which the mayor Pierluigi Biondi took part together with other representatives of the civic assise and the national, regional and local institutions.
&nbsp;
The brazier installed inside the fountain that is located in the center of the memorial was lit by two young eagles, born in 2009, year of the earthquake, and both attending the conservatory "A. Casella" of the capital of Abruzzo, Elisa Nardi and Tommaso Sponta, while the beam of light in memory of the victims was lit from the courtyard of the municipal office of Palazzo Margherita Duomo because of the works of revimentation in Corso Square
&nbsp;
"The memories, in these fifteen years, were our silent and discreet companions, who guided us in the choices towards the rebirth of our city, were our inner compass. - it has emphasized the first citizen - who is free from that past are the born after the tragic event and we have the moral duty to think of them, helping them to make of memory the substance of their own identity, putting into being the pure activity of rammemorare. As symbolically they did, this evening at the Parco della Memoria, two very young students of our Conservatory, Elisa and Thomas. Memory is a elsewhere that envelops our present and we eagles are our memory."
&nbsp;
"I was just born when there was the earthquake and I experienced this tremendous experience through the story of my parents. I am proud to be able to participate in this celebration and remember with all of you the victims of this tremendous earthquake," said Elisa Nardi. "I feel privileged to be present here this evening, representing the children of my age. Although I can't remember that night, my family's stories allowed me to imagine the fear and pain of those moments. During these years I also listened to the stories of older friends and boys. From their words I felt the fatigue and determination they had in wanting to return and stay in L'Aquila. This desire for rebirth allowed the city of L'Aquila to regain its beauty. I think, moreover, that, despite the earthquake left indelible marks in our city, this event has somehow contributed to strengthen ties in our community," said Tommaso Sponta.
&nbsp;
After the ignition of the brazier, at the Parco della Memoria, was read the names of the victims of the earthquake and in the church of Santa Maria del Suffragio, in Piazza Duomo, the Holy Mass presided over by the Metropolitan Archbishop of L'Aquila and president of the Ceam (Abruzzese-Molisana Episcopal Conference), Cardinal Giuseppe Petrocchi with reading of the names during the Eucharistic prayer. Before the blessing, the first citizen read some of his personal reflections contained in a message addressed to citizenship. At 3:32, time of the earthquake of 6 April 2009, the bell of the church played 309 riots in honor of those who lost their lives so years ago.&nbsp;
<h2>Mattarella, memory tragedy for full reconstruction
"The earthquake of fifteen years ago, in the night between 5 and 6 April, upset L'Aquila and the surrounding area, tearing more than 300 people to life. The destruction fell on the old town, on the outskirts, on the neighboring villages, leaving the whole national community attonished and upset. The country knew how to react, mobilizing all its energies, while the inhabitants of the area affected by the earthquake found strength to start rebuilding houses, workplaces, schools, to recover, as far as possible, the artistic beauties." To say it is the President of the Republic, Sergio Mattarella.
<h2>Melons, wounded we got up and back stronger
"The rebirth of the Eagle is the rebirth of a piece of ourselves. Fifteen years ago we were injured but we were able to get up and get stronger." Giorgia Meloni says this in a passage of the statement in which he recalls that "today Italy pays tribute to the victims of the earthquake and is tightened to the Aquilana and Abruzzo community, to those who lost the most dear affections and to all those who, with tenacity and determination, contributed to the rebirth of the city".
&nbsp;
"L'Aquila is a model, for the response that the state has given since the management of the emergency, passing through reconstruction until the regeneration of the last years, of which the first effects are seen," he adds. "I address a thought to the many who, in various titles and in the different stages, have contributed: the Italians who showed great solidarity and closeness; the volunteers who mobilized in the next days and months; women and men, institutions and not, who with self-denial and commitment have helped to carry out a reconstruction that has become an example," says the President of the Council.

