AGI - Who said sustainability is just a slogan? They do not think so in Scarlino, where they chose to grow the territory by focusing on conscious tourism and ecological ethics. From 19 to 21 April, the Municipality in the province of Grosseto becomes for three days the capital of environmental sustainability with 'Let's save the Planet Festival', an interdisciplinary review that will lead in the ancient village of Maremma personality of culture, economy, journalism, physics to promote sustainable lifestyles and to confront on topics and best practices for the energy transition and safeguarding the environment.
The exhibition will see all the municipal territory protagonist of theatrical performances, music, presentations of books, workshops, talk shows, conferences and seminars. The three days will have its highlight in the national seminar ‘The culture of sustainability at the time of the energy transition’. An opportunity to share good practices, through the contribution of experts and industry specialists, to reduce the environmental impact and make more equitable, inclusive and sustainable museums, public and private historical buildings, businesses and territories.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
Medieval village enclosed between coast and hinterland in the middle of the Maremma Tuscany, Scarlino had already gone in counter-tendenza in the summer of 2021 when, first and still only case of the Region, decided to make the most loved and photographed beach of its coast, Cala Violina. Undisputed Queen of the Maremma summers, the cove risked to see her beauty compromised because of the large number of visitors who crowded her in search of the most instagramable shot.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
“At first we had all against, now we realized that preserving the genuineness of the places is the right way to grow the territories - says the mayor Francesca Travison –. With access to the beach only by reservation, we have attracted a 'slow' and conscious tourist flow, which also grows in the periods off season and which does not stop at the coast, but also visits the historic village of Scarlino, the Padule fauna oasis and the Archaeological Museum of the Portus Scabris".
In line with this philosophy, 'Let's save the Planet Festival' is part of the wider cultural program 'Scarlino Oltrecielo. The beauty that welcomes a calendar of seasonally adjusted free events, which started in January. “An ambitious project that has more objectives, cultural, tourist and economic – explains the mayor – in this way the community of Scarlino becomes the ambassador of its municipality. During the recent inauguration of Pesaro Capital of Culture, the president of the Italian Republic Sergio Mattarella highlighted the importance of regaining consciousness of our ancient and robust roots. This is why it is essential to believe in culture without separating it from everyday life and investing in values, to trust in ethics, equity and sustainable growth. To admire beauty, to urge ingenuity, to exalt creative thinking creates communities and stimulates a collective thought aimed at the common good.”
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
“Culture is knowledge, but also awareness. They need courage and vision to embark on the paths of change. Ours is a very vast territory, which includes ancient parts and more recent places, tradition and innovation, where the beauty of history and nature play a fundamental role – concludes Travison. We like to think that this beauty, which goes beyond any spatial-temporal reference, can contribute to ‘stop time’ for those who decide to visit us.
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
