AGI - In the mountains of Trentino the growth of the population of bears has reached 98 specimens for an annual increase of 10%> being there also 13 puppies. This is what emerged from the report of great carnivores written by the Autonomous Province of Trento. Bears are increasingly frequented by anthropized forests. If the bear females remain permanently in the western part of Trentino, the 53 males are also found in the eastern territories. Recently the Province of Trento has approved a bill that will allow the maximum reduction of 8 specimens for the years 2024 and 2025 if considered "problematic", that is "confident with the human being". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp;"The words serve little, especially at times like this that make the pain reawaken but I would like to say that our response, after the drama of a year ago, was and is in the sign of the even stronger commitment to try to give a turn to a situation that we first define unsustainable". The provincial council member Roberto Failoni, with delegation, among others, to forests and hunting, on the occasion of the first anniversary of the death of Andrea Papi following the attack by a bear on the mountains of Trentino. Papi, 26 years of Caldes, is the first victim in Italy following the attack of a bear in the last century.
<br> "The Province of Trento is close to the Papi family and the Val di Sole community - says Failoni -. We know that no one is allowed to go back but it is ahead that we want to look, with courage, determination and all the attention that we will be able to give in respect of those who are paying more, like the family of Andrea, but also in the search for a sustainable balance between man and nature". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2> The memory of the fiancée
&nbsp;"Andrea I want to remind you every day of my life except today, to have a memory in the heart of every day, except today. Today there is no positive emotion to transmit, today the memory is only what each of us has tried, who that night, who the next day, when they knew, pain, screaming, unbelief. Today we only remember what you might have felt at that time, pain, fear, anger, I don't want to know." These are the particularly touching phrases that Alessia Gregori wrote in a long post on social media in recalling her boyfriend Andrea Papi of 26 years that in the afternoon of the tragic 5 April last year was attacked and wounded to death by the bear 'Jj4' in the woods of Caldes in Val di Sole in Trentino. The plantigrado from 18 April last is enclosed in a fence of the Casteller faunal center in Trento Sud. The animal was sentenced to death but the ordinance was suspended to follow the memories and recurrence of animal associations.
&nbsp;
"We did up and down the road 100 times, going down with disappointment but also the relief of not finding you - Gregori continued remembering April 5, 2023 -. Then again that cold bench, a thousand questions in the head, the screams of the friends who were looking for you to feel all over the country. 5 hours in which awareness mounted in everyone, looks of reassurance and fear, cigarettes turned off in half and turned on immediately, cold inside and out."
&nbsp;
The girlfriend then described the time when she learned the news. "They found something, silence, silence, silence. A carabiniere takes off the cap and invites us to sit down: they found it - writes the fiancée -. Finally the wait is over, unfortunately life is over. The heart breaks, but rests. Today we only remember what you might have felt at that time, pain, fear, anger, I don't want to know." The message ends: "Thinking with a smile today is not possible, today it is all dark, but tomorrow you will be light and courage for all, for those who leave everything and go away, for those who try to start again, for those who every day tells of the 'zio Andreà, for those who wait for the toast of his birthday, for those who pray, for those who fight and for those who reborn. So Andre today I greet you, we'll take care of tomorrow, and always."&nbsp;

